What you need to know:  He burst onto the global stage at just 17 by scoring dazzling goals, including two in the final against hosts Sweden, as Brazil won the World Cup for the first time in 1958.He went on to have one of the most storied careers in sport, scoring more than 1,000 goals before retiring in 1977."As I have been doing monthly, I am going to the hospital to continue my treatment," Pele said on his social media platforms on February 13.